@Rahul Ahire That’s exactly the question. Clearly you’ve learned nothing about this language. Like Latin, COBOL has survived for a reason, despite being called a dead language for decades. 
If you’re just learning it today, you’ll likely never be as proficient as those that learned it decades ago because you don’t have the patience for it. 
That’s why it’s going to keep surviving, just like Latin.
